People with purging disorder, Keel said, are of normal weight, and they purge after eating normal or small amounts of food.
Poor body image dating to a swim meet Amanda won when she was 7 led to her battle with eating disorders.
To date, there are no approved medications to treat binge-eating disorder, but a large, multi-center study may offer hope to the 2 percent of the population who suffer from it.
In the meantime, people like Amanda will continue the daily struggle to keep their disorder in check.
